      {
        "name": "A. P.  Mosk",
        "email": "",
        "affiliation": ""
      }
    ],
    "abstract": "Quantum Readout of Physical Unclonable Functions (PUFs) is a recently introduced method for remote authentication of objects.\nWe present an extension of the protocol to enable the authentication of data: a verifier can check if received classical data was sent by the PUF holder. We call this modification QR-d or, in the case of the optical-PUF implementation, QSA-d.\nWe discuss how QSA-d can be operated in a parallel way. We also present a protocol for authenticating quantum states.",
    "keywords": [
      "Physical Unclonable Functions",
      "quantum security"
    ],
